Package: groundhog
Type: Package
Title: R Client for "groundhog" (Elevation API)
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("James", "Lamb", email = "jaylamb20@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Brad", "Beechler", email = "brad.beechler@uptake.com", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: James Lamb <jaylamb20@gmail.com>
Description: "groundhog" is a service which provides access to
             SRTM elevation data. This package is a complement for that service.
             Given a data.table with GPS information, this package provides utilities
             to enrich that dataset with elevation and slope features.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0)
Imports:
    assertthat,
    data.table,
    futile.logger,
    httr,
    jsonlite,
    uuid
Suggests:
    knitr,
    testthat
License: file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
